description: JsTrace allows you to heavily instrument your JavaScript code without flooding the console with messages. It has "Trace Levels" (off, error, warn, info, debug, log), which allow you to fine-tune what amount of trace information comes out of each area or module of your code. It additionally supports a callback function to allow further processing of Trace messages.  It is cross-browser and will gracefully degrade down to "console.log" on browsers without support for higher level methods like console.error.
releaseNotes:
Added Trace.config method for single-call configuration from the client
      Added RequireJS/AMD support
      Minor fix for non-browser usage
summary: A simple pure JavaScript utility for "switched" tracing (a la System.Diagnostics.TraceSource).
